  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Admin Assistant cum Property Officer",
  "description": "<p>Are you an organized and detail-oriented professional with experience in property management? Join our team as an <strong>Admin Assistant cum Property Officer</strong> and play a vital role in keeping operations smooth and efficient!</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible and coordinating the day-to-day maintenance and  \noperations of the estate</li><li>Ensure compliance with all building statutory regulations and acts</li><li>Observe and comply with the estate's house rules and bylaws</li><li>Through regular checks and inspections, reivew and recommend repair / replacement / improvement works for the properties managed. </li><li>To monitor the esate's agreements, licences, insurance, and term contractors' contract expiry for renewal         </li><li>Manage the procurement process involved in the eatates managed</li><li>Tracking and monitoring repair and replacement works for regular updates / checks.     </li><li>Provide essential customer service support to the residents and owners</li><li>Coordinate and attend Council Meetings and General Meetings      </li><li>To follow up on matters discussed / decided after meetings</li><li>To prepare weekly / monthly estate's report including service providers' performance and feedback, owners' feedback, matter update and utilities' consumption etc</li><li>Main proper records and file of correspondence and documents    </li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum O-Level qualification.</li><li>At least 1 year of relevant working experience in property management.</li><li>Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to manage maintenance tasks efficiently.</li><li>Detail-oriented and committed to safety and compliance.</li></ul><p>🔹 Interested candidates, please apply by writing in to hr@absolutprop.com. Only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</p><p><br /></p><p>Join us and contribute to the seamless management of our properties!</p>",
